@node install "Installation:"
        You'll need rexxarplib.library in libs: (It's available in many places)
        Then copy @{"libs/RexxDosSupport.library" system "more RexxDosSupport.doc"} to libs:
            (I included this because it isn't available everywhere)

        Then copy rndfile where ever you put you ARexx scripts.
@endnode

@node usage "Usage:"

rndfile @{b}Paths/M,Pattern/K,Command/K,CmdOptions/K,ALL/S,DIRS/S,FILES/S@{ub}

       You do *not* need to put a '/' at the end of the Path.

@{b}    Paths/M@{ub}     :   Specify any number of paths for rndfile to search through.
                    e.g. Work:Docs/
                    Default is the current directory.

    @{b}Pattern/K@{ub}   :   An Arp pattern for rndfile to apply to the
                    list of files/dirs.
                    e.g. s#?.txt
                    Default is '~(#?.info)' No info files.

    @{b}Command/K@{ub}   :   A program that rndfile will run on the chose file.
                    e.g. PPShow
                    Default is the enviroment variable @{"DefRndCmd" link install} or 'c:list'
                    You can set your own default command with:
                        setenv DefRndCmd <command>

    @{b}CmdOptions/K@{ub}:   Options to pass to the Command program.
                    e.g. SCREEN
                    Defaults to null string. (Nothing)

    @{b}ALL/S@{ub}       :   Allow directories OR files to be chosen.
                    This is the default option.

    @{b}DIRS/S@{ub}      :   Allow only directories to be chosen.

    @{b}FILES/S@{ub}     :   Allow only files to be chosen.
@endnode

@node examples "Examples:"
    @{fg highlight}RX rndfile@{fg text}
        uses default command 'c:list' on a file in the current directory

    @{fg highlight}RX rndfile Sounds:Samples/ Pictures:Things Command=delete All@{fg text}
        uses delete command on a random File OR Directory in those dir

    @{fg highlight}RX rndfile Sounds:Samples/ Command=Multiview CmdOptions="SCREEN BACKDROP"@{fg text}
        uses Multiview program with SCREEN and BACKDROP options
        in Sound:Samples/
@endnode

