@endnode

@node history "History:"
            @{b}2.10@{ub}    Just a few small additions.
                +   You can now have multiple paths. @{"(See Examples)" link examples}
                +   Now will read the default command from the env-variable
                    @{"DefRndCmd" link usage}.
            @{b}2.00@{ub}    @{fg highlight}Hooboy!@{fg text} Completely re-wrote the program. It's like a
                    completely new program.
                +   Replaced ugly argument parsing structure with
                    ReadArgs() from @{"RexxDosSupport.library" system "more RexxDosSupport.doc"}.
                +   Now I use a real template.
                +   Replaced '.info' removing routines with FileList()
                    from rexxarplib.library.
                -   Now also checks for ':' instead of just '/'
                    No more 'Can't find Path SYS:/'

            @{b}1.10@{ub}    Fixed instructions/comments

            @{b}1.00@{ub}    I wrote this for the Amiga users on @{"alt.tv.animaniacs" link pinkulus}
                    so they could play a collection of 'Wheel of Morality'
                    samples. Unfortunately, I wrote this before looking at
                    the sample collection. This program is useless for that.
                    But it did make a useful utility.
@endnode

